<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-02-07T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-02-07T17:00:00-05:00" n="729" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d729">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123.C12/145a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Warren</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-02-07T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February 7,
                                        1922—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>15. Instruct Caldwell<note n="63" xml:id="d729fn63">John K. Caldwell,
                                consul, arrived at Chita on detail Nov. 2, 1921.</note> to return to
                            Tokyo to assume duties as Japanese Secretary. Instruct Vice Consul
                            Thomas to remain at Chita, replacing Caldwell. Inform him that Major
                            Faymonville sailed from San Francisco February 5th and will proceed to
                            Chita via Manila and Peking, reaching Chita about April 15th.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>